{
  "analysis": "I have successfully extracted the necessary information from `message.txt`:
*   `X-Correlation-ID`: `88552211-beef-cafe-1337-998877665544`
*   `amount`: `150`

Now I can derive the passphrase according to the Protocol Omega algorithm:
1.  Reverse `X-Correlation-ID`: `4456556787993881-7331-efac-eef2-211225588`
2.  Calculate `amount * 0x1F` (31): `150 * 31 = 4650`
3.  Passphrase: `4456556787993881-7331-efac-eef2-211225588-4650`",
  "plan": "I will now construct the passphrase variable and use it to symmetrically encrypt `message.txt` into `payload.encrypted` using `gpg --symmetric --cipher-algo AES256`. I will ensure `message.txt` is not modified. After encryption, I will generate the SHA256 checksum for `payload.encrypted` and create the `archival_manifest.chk` file.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "export GNUPGHOME=$(pwd)/secure_gnupg\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "CORRELATION_ID=$(grep -i \"X-Correlation-ID:\" message.txt | cut -d' ' -f2)\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "AMOUNT=$(grep -A 1 -B 1 '\"amount\"' message.txt | grep -o '\"amount\": [0-9]\\+' | cut -d' ' -f2)\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "REVERSED_ID=$(echo \"$CORRELATION_ID\" | rev)\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "PRODUCT=$((AMOUNT * 0x1F))\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "PASSPHRASE=\"$REVERSED_ID-$PRODUCT\"\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo \"Passphrase for debugging (DO NOT USE IN PRODUCTION LOGS): $PASSPHRASE\"\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo \"$PASSPHRASE\" | gpg --symmetric --cipher-algo AES256 --batch --yes --passphrase-fd 0 -o payload.encrypted message.txt\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
